compile using main.c and archive library file

cc	*.o		main.c		-L.		libftprintf.a

Command explained.
-----------------------
Compile and link all .o files with main.c, using the library libftprintf.a located in the current directory (   -L.   ).

-L path: 	Adds the specified directory to the list of directories to be searched 
			for libraries during linking.
current directory (.).

Requirement for this command.
----------------------------------
1,	This assumes you do not have main() in ft_printf 
	or have a main.c included in Makefile.
2,	This assumes, you have *.o files of all required c files.
3,	And this assumes you have generated the libftprintf.a library.

